SUMMARY:Timmy No Brakes LIVE at Pittsburgh Improv
DTSTAMP:20260701T033035Z
DTSTART:20260703T190000Z
DESCRIPTION:Official TicketsResale Tickets \nAbout the Performer\nTimmy No 
	Brakes is comedy’s most unhinged rising star. A Kill Tony viral menace and
	 Golden Ticket winner\, Timmy has exploded onto the national comedy scene 
	with his off-the-rails energy and deranged confidence that has audiences l
	osing it from the first moment he hits the stage. \nKnown for his high-oct
	ane rants\, heterosexual character work\, and pure uncut stupidity deliver
	ed with absolute conviction\, Timmy No Brakes is the kind of comedian you 
	have to see live to truly believe. His Kill Tony appearances have racked u
	p millions of views online\, turning him into one of the most talked-about
	 new voices in stand-up comedy. \nIf you’re looking for a comedy show that
	’s completely unpredictable\, wildly funny\, and unlike anything you’ve se
	en before\, Timmy No Brakes is your guy. Buckle up — this show is going to
	 be a ride. \nEvent Details\nDate: Friday\, July 3\, 2026 \nTime: 7:00 PM 
	(Doors open at 5:30 PM) \nVenue: Pittsburgh Improv\, 166 E. Bridge St\, Ho
	mestead\, PA 15120 \nAge Restriction: Ages 21 and up \nAdditional Shows: A
	 late show is also available at 9:30 PM on Friday\, July 3\, and two shows
	 on Saturday\, July 4 at 6:30 PM and 9:00 PM. \nAbout the Venue\nThe Pitts
	burgh Improv is located at 166 E. Bridge Street in Homestead\, PA — just m
	inutes from downtown Pittsburgh. As part of the nationally recognized Impr
	ov Comedy Club chain\, the Pittsburgh Improv is one of the premier comedy 
	venues in the region. \nThe club features a full-service restaurant and ba
	r\, making it a perfect destination for a complete night out. The intimate
	 showroom seats approximately 300 guests\, ensuring every seat has a great
	 sightline to the stage. The venue’s lively atmosphere is ideal for the ki
	nd of high-energy comedy that Timmy No Brakes delivers. \nParking is avail
	able nearby\, and the venue is easily accessible from major highways. Note
	 that this show falls on the July 4th holiday weekend\, so plan ahead for 
	traffic and parking. The Pittsburgh Improv is known for bringing top natio
	nal touring comedians to the Pittsburgh area. \nWhat to Expect\nTimmy No B
	rakes delivers a stand-up performance that is completely unhinged\, wildly
	 energetic\, and absolutely hilarious. This is a solo stand-up show — expe
	ct 60–75 minutes of non-stop\, unpredictable comedy that will have you in 
	tears. \nHis shows are known for being spontaneous and electric. Timmy’s c
	omedy blends absurdist character work with rapid-fire observations and cro
	wd interaction. No two shows are the same\, and Pittsburgh audiences are i
	n for a treat on the July 4th holiday weekend. \nPlease note: This is an a
	ges 21 and up event. Valid ID is required at the door. Third-party tickets
	 will not be honored — purchase only from authorized sellers. \nTicket Inf
	ormation\nPrice Range: $25 – $69 (plus fees) \nTickets are available throu
	gh official channels and resale marketplaces. This show falls on the July 
	4th holiday weekend\, so tickets are expected to sell quickly. Purchase ea
	rly to secure your spot! \nOfficial TicketsResale Tickets \nThis post cont
	ains affiliate links. We may earn a commission at no extra cost to you.\n\
	nhttps://comedycalendar.com/event/timmy-no-brakes-live-at-pittsburgh-impro
	v/\n\nFrom Comedy Calendar
URL:https://comedycalendar.com/event/timmy-no-brakes-live-at-pittsburgh-imp
	rov/
LOCATION:Pittsburgh Improv\, 166 E. Bridge St\, Homestead\, Pennsylvania\, 
	15120\, United States
