UID:81NJKt5Dxy38BJtM0FdaP
SUMMARY:Red\, White & Cruise (SOLD OUT!)
DTSTAMP:20260701T033035Z
DTSTART:20260704T203000Z
DESCRIPTION:THIS EVENT HAS SOLD OUT! IF YOU WOULD LIKE TO BE PLACED ON A WA
	ITLIST IF ANY SPOTS OPEN UP\, PLEASE EMAIL INFO@HERMANNPARK.ORG.\nJoin us 
	for Red\, White & Cruise where you can watch Miller Outdoor Theatre’s fire
	works show light up the sky from the peaceful waters of Hermann Park\, wit
	h a special pedal boat rental from 8:30–10:30 p.m. on Saturday\, July 4! \
	nAs we celebrate 250 years of American independence\, gather your crew and
	 watch the sky come alive with fireworks while cruising across the lake in
	 your own pedal boat under the stars. \nSaturday\, July 4\n8:30 – 10:30 p.
	m.  \n🎟️ $150 per boat (up to 4 people) includes:\n🕘 Boat rental up to 2 ho
	urs\n🍿 Drinks & snacks\n🎊 Festive accessories\n🅿️ Reserved parking in Lot I
	 near Lake Plaza\n⛵ Board anytime between 8:30–9:30 p.m. and enjoy the sho
	w from the water (fireworks begin at approximately 9:45 p.m.\, boats must 
	return once fireworks finish) \nBOOK YOUR BOAT HERE!  \n🚨 Important Info: 
	\n\nOne rider per boat must be 18+\nAll riders 18+ must sign a digital wai
	ver before boarding\nAt least one rider must be 18+\, with a physical gove
	rnment ID\, and sign a waiver before boarding\nTickets are non-refundable\
	nEvent is rain or shine per Miller Outdoor Theatre’s plan\nIn the event of
	 lightning\, pedal boats will close\, and refunds will be issued \n\nThe p
	urchase of a ticket includes an up-to 2-hour pedal boat ride for up to 4 p
	eople to enjoy the sight of Miller Outdoor Theatre’s fireworks show\, drin
	ks\, snacks\, festive treats\, and a reserved parking spot in Lot I near L
	ott Hall by Lake Plaza (starting at 8 p.m.). Only one ticket purchase of $
	150 is needed for a 4-person boat (i.e. it is the cost per boat\, not per 
	rider).  \nA reminder that at least one rider per boat must be 18 years or
	 older.  All riders 18 years or older must sign a digital waiver before bo
	arding. Tickets are non-refundable. We are following Miller Outdoor Theatr
	e’s plan for their event and fireworks show which is rain or shine. If the
	re is lightning in the area\, we will close the pedal boats and ticket hol
	ders will receive a refund.  \nPlease arrive early to allow time to park i
	n Lot I as roads in the Park will be closed by HPD and closures are subjec
	t to change based on their purview.  \n\nhttps://hermannpark.org/event/red
	-white-cruise-2/\n\nFrom Hermann Park Conservancy
URL:https://hermannpark.org/event/red-white-cruise-2/
LOCATION:Lake Plaza
