UID:pEP1FWx4tfdaN1A1kdlPu
SUMMARY:Opossums & Popsicles
DTSTAMP:20260701T033036Z
DTSTART:20260718T183000Z
DESCRIPTION:$37 member / $52 nonmember / $22 children ages 5-12Instructor: 
	Wildlife Center of TexasAges 5+ \n\n\n\nChill out with some of the coolest
	 critters around! Grab a frozen treat\, enjoy a refreshing root beer (or r
	egular beer) from Saint Arnold Brewing Company\, and get up close and pers
	onal with live wild animals from Wildlife Center of Texas. You’ll learn al
	l about Houston’s amazing urban wildlife – including opossums – and then y
	ou’ll go on a guided hike to enjoy a truly wild night out. \n\n\n\nPlease 
	dress for the weather and wear walking shoes \n\n\n\n\nRegister online\n\n
	\n\n\n\n\n\n\nInstructor Bio: The Wildlife Center of Texas is one of the l
	argest rehabilitation centers in the country\, admitting nearly 10\,000 wi
	ld patients each year. Its mission is to care for all injured\, orphaned\,
	 ill\, and oiled wildlife through wildlife rehabilitation\, public educati
	on\, and oiled wildlife response.\n\nhttps://houstonarboretum.org/event/op
	ossums-popsicles/\n\nFrom Houston Arboretum & Nature Center
URL:https://houstonarboretum.org/event/opossums-popsicles/
X-CALRIPPER-SOURCE:houston-arboretum
CATEGORIES:Houston Arboretum & Nature Center
TRANSP:TRANSPARENT
DURATION:PT2H
END:VEVENT
